args:
The prince and his allies manage to defeat the
demonic otherworldly Ramiel—but when the
miasma flowing from the sealing stone revives
him anew, they're forced to continue the battle.
Guess that was easier done than said.\nYou had me worried when you said we\nhad no chance against this guy, Ramiel!
I hate to dampen the celebration,\nbut this is not yet over.
Unless we sever the bond tying that man\nto the stone, the demon will resurrect in\nmere moments.
The only way to break said link is to\ncontain the miasma pouring from it—\nbut alas, the volume is far too great.
What about all the holy water we have?
Most humans can't so much as approach\nthe stone in this state. Any holy water\nwould simply evaporate on contact.
Then I'll do it. This is an apostle's job\nanyway, so I'll use my mana to contain\nthe stone's miasma by force.

Holy Goddess, grant me now the glory
of thy name. Make my soul thy net,
my hands thy shackles, my voice thy lock
to bind the impure with thy sacred...
Hot damn. This thing is STRONG.
Nevin ain't lookin' so hot there!\nIs he gonna be okay?
I am afraid that even Nevin's power\ncannot hope to contain so much...
I TOLD you, I am also an apostle!\nIf one is not enough, then we must\nwork to contain this evil together!
Don't suppose this is the time for foolish\npride, huh? All right, let's do this!
Whoa! The two of them are actually\nforcing the miasma back!
(What two of us? This is all Pinon!\nHow does she have so much power?!)
Just a bit more... Just a... GRAAAAGH!
Oh, you gotta be KIDDIN' me!
Aaaaah ha ha ha! Oh, how pathetic you\nmust feel to see your one chance snatched\naway from you at the moment of victory!
We're not done—we'll defeat you as many\ntimes as it takes to seal that evil away!
Bold words, Prince. But I have absorbed\nmore miasma than before, and my power\ngrows greater by the second.
Plus, I never make the same mistake\ntwice—so I will ensure that the stone\nstays forever out of your reach!
He's opening a tear in space!
I have seen the stone safely back to my\nchurch—which is a great distance away.
Like the bond you apostles and archangels\nshare through your Sigils, my link to the\nsealing stone is unaffected by distance.
So long as that bond remains, I am\nundying—and you fools have no means\nof severing that tie!
My defeat is now impossible...\njust as your deaths are inevitable!
There's gotta be SOME way to take this\ndirty cheater down!
I fear all is as he says; we had one chance\nto defeat him, and now it is lost.
So long as the stone's miasma goes\nuncontained, the demon is invincible.\nAnd as the stone is here no longer...
Then we truly have no recourse?!
Aaaah ha ha ha ha! Yes! Despair!\nLament as you prostrate yourselves\nbefore the demon's boundless might!
That's a wicked look, even for you.\nDoes this involve Sandalphon somehow?

You are all in for quite the sight. For now,
banish worry of the stone from your minds
and simply enjoy raining blows down upon
that abomination.
Oh, is that all we need to do?
Ah, perfect timing. It turns out I have a\nmessage from dear old Basileus.\nIt reads: ＂Do not disappoint me.＂
Well then? You heard the man.
Wait, that means he has high expectations\nfor us, right?! We can assume that?!
In that case, I shall hold nothing back!\nHRAAAAAAAGH!
Whoa, look at the kid go!\nShe's even sharper than before.
She's getting even stronger.\nThis has to be...
Rather than taking in the show, you should\nlearn from her example and give your all\nto the fight in front of you.
I was just thinking about how to pull all of\nPinon's potential out at once. If it works,\nshe might even be a match for Basileus.
That's quite the bar to set. But if she\nCOULD harness the strength she's shown\nglimpses of... Well, you may be right.
She's at her strongest when she feels the\ntrust and expectations of others on her.\nJust a theory, of course, but still...
Heh. I see you are enjoying this.
Well, I definitely like the part where her\ngetting better makes my life easier.
Then let us leave it at that, if you wish.
I don't know WHAT you're insinuating.\nSheesh. No wonder folks call you wicked.
You two wanna knock off the stand-up\nroutine and give us a hand here?!
I've told you people: I'm an ideas man.
As an apostle, it wouldn't hurt to rise to\nyour allies' expectations for once.

Don't remember that in the job
description... Eh, but the mission
is the mission, I guess. Time for
us to make one last stand.
I am the apostle Nevin, one hand of the\nGoddess, and I shall see Her will done!
